    "Although known for his bombastic and even at times bullying style, he managed to raise many private funds for the museum, known as the \"Greek Garage\" to locals, even after the crash of the stock market in 1929.": [],
    "He successfully handled the public reaction to the purchase for what was then a great deal of money for C\u00e9zanne large canvas, <em>The Bathers</em>, bought during the height of the Depression.": [],
    "He retired from the Museum in 1955 and was succeeded by <a href=\"/marceauh\">Henri Marceau</a>.": [],
    "Kimball suffered a heart attack in Ravenna, Italy while collecting material for a book, and died in a Munich hospital where he had been taken.Kimball represents a genre of man-of-action art historian/administrator that came to be during the first half of the 20the century.": [
